This paper focuses on measuring the level of maintenance activity of open source projects on GitHub, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also uses machine learning models to define a metric for measuring maintenance activity, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper analyzes the historical evolution of projects, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI) categories.
